                     <interp inst="t18280911-324-defend1764" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for <rs id="t18280911-324-off1662" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-324-off1662" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-324-off1662" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18280911-324-cd1663" type="crimeDate">13th of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-324-off1662 t18280911-324-cd1663"></join>, 1 saw, value 8s., the goods of 
                     <persName id="t18280911-324-victim1765" type="victimName">
                        John 
                        Farrow
                     <interp inst="t18280911-324-victim1765" type="surname" value="Farrow"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18280911-324-victim1765" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18280911-324-victim1765" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-324-off1662 t18280911-324-victim1765"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , to whom he was servant
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>JOHN FARROW. I am a <rs id="t18280911-324-viclabel1664" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-324-victim1765 t18280911-324-viclabel1664"></join>; the prisoner was in my employ; I lost a saw on the 13th of August, while I was at breakfast - I had seen it ten minutes before eight o'clock, and when I returned it was gone.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Did you owe this poor man any money? A. There was a little difference; I did not owe him 1l. 11d.; I do not know that I owed him any - I gave him 15s. on the Saturday; he not did work on the Monday and Tuesday; he came on Tuesday and asked me for money, but I would not give him any - I owed him none.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-324-person1766">
                  BENJAMIN 
                  LEE
               <interp inst="t18280911-324-person1766" type="surname" value="LEE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-324-person1766" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-324-person1766" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. On the 13th of August the prisoner pawned this saw.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-324-person1767">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HOLT
               <interp inst="t18280911-324-person1767" type="surname" value="HOLT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-324-person1767" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-324-person1767" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I apprehended the prisoner, and found the duplicate of the saw on him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. When he paid me 15s. he said<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182809110162"></xptr>the work must be stopped, as the gentleman would not pay for it; I went on Monday and asked if I was to go on with it - he gave me no answer; I went again on Tuesday. he would not tell me then, and I took the saw to raise 2s. which I wanted - he owes me 22s.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-324-person1768">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BARNETT
               <interp inst="t18280911-324-person1768" type="surname" value="BARNETT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-324-person1768" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-324-person1768" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I know the prisoner; I work for Farrow. I was at the prosecutor's on Monday; heard him ask for money - Farrow promised he should have some before the day was out; he said on Saturday he was short, and could not pay us, and could only let the prisoner have 15s. - he owed him about 1l. or more from what I saw him do.</p>
               <p>COURT. Q. Do you work for Farrow now? A. No, I could get no wages, and left him. <rs id="t18280911-324-verdict1665" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-324-verdict1665" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               NOT GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
